    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD, a pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering. This example retains its original 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, delivering linear power delivery across the rev range with no vacuum line degradation or boost leaks. The chassis remains structurally flawless, benefiting from a near-perfect 50/50 weight distribution and a sophisticated double-wishbone suspension setup that provides unmatched tactile feedback. This unit features the factory Torsen limited-slip differential and 5-speed manual transmission, both operating with mechanical crispness. Meticulously maintained with documented compression tests showing optimal apex seal health, this front-midship icon is free of any aftermarket modifications. A rare opportunity to own a preserved masterpiece of lightweight, high-output design.",
      "price": 47500.0,
